<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIS RECORD IS GREAT, EXCEPT FOR JANUARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In rebuttal to Mr. Cowdery's letter (Jan. 7), saying the championship of L.A. 
should not be decided until after the bowl games: 
</P>
<P>
The last 2 years, USC has defeated UCLA with the Rose Bowl on the line for both 
teams. Since UCLA lost those games they had to settle for a lesser bowl, and 
thus, a lesser opponent. 
</P>
<P>
Let UCLA brag about beating up on the BYUs and Floridas in other bowl games. 
For Pac-10 teams, the Rose Bowl is the big show, and you can't win it unless 
you get there. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN RIS 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
